1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,366
你有没有觉得AI特别懂你
Have you ever felt like AI really gets you

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:04,200
打开ChatGPT
Open ChatGPT

3
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,366
问它一个问题
Ask it a question

4
00:00:05,666 --> 00:00:06,833
它给你一个答案
It gives you an answer

5
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:07,800
你看了看
You take a look

6
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:10,500
觉得嗯有道理
Think hmm that makes sense

7
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:12,533
然后你就按它说的做了
And then you just do what it says

8
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:13,766
买什么基金
What fund to buy

9
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,233
选什么工作
What job to choose

10
00:00:15,366 --> 00:00:16,700
怎么跟老板谈判
How to negotiate with your boss

11
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:18,133
你越来越依赖它
You rely on it more and more

12
00:00:18,366 --> 00:00:21,900
但今天我要告诉你一个你可能不愿意承认的事实
But today I want to tell you a truth you might not want to admit

13
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,433
当你在用AI做决策的时候
When you use AI to make decisions

14
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,433
你的大脑正在被三个认知偏差操控
Your brain is being manipulated by three cognitive biases

15
00:00:28,566 --> 00:00:30,333
你不仅没有变得更聪明
Not only are you not getting smarter

16
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:31,900
反而可能变得更蠢了
You might actually be getting dumber

17
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,200
这不是我瞎说
I am not making this up

18
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,866
诺贝尔经济学奖得主丹尼尔·卡尼曼
Nobel Prize winner in Economics Daniel Kahneman

19
00:00:35,866 --> 00:00:38,133
研究了一辈子人的决策偏差
Spent his whole life studying human decision biases

20
00:00:38,366 --> 00:00:39,166
他发现
He found that

21
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:41,566
人的大脑有两套系统
The human brain has two systems

22
00:00:41,766 --> 00:00:42,566
系统一
System one

23
00:00:42,566 --> 00:00:43,000
快
Fast

24
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:43,733
直觉
Intuitive

25
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:44,700
情绪化
Emotional

26
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:45,700
系统二
System two

27
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,266
慢
Slow

28
00:00:46,266 --> 00:00:47,100
理性
Rational

29
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,033
需要费力
Requires effort

30
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,166
问题来了
Here is the problem

31
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:50,766
当你打开AI
When you open AI

32
00:00:50,766 --> 00:00:52,633
拿到一个现成答案的时候
And get a ready made answer

33
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:53,966
你的系统一
Your system one

34
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:55,433
也就是直觉
That is your intuition

35
00:00:55,966 --> 00:00:56,800
会怎么做
What does it do

36
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:57,966
它会偷懒
It takes the easy way out

37
00:00:58,133 --> 00:01:01,033
它会直接把AI的答案当成自己的判断
It directly adopts AIs answer as its own judgment

38
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:03,100
你觉得自己在做决策
You think you are making decisions

39
00:01:03,733 --> 00:01:06,100
其实你只是AI的复读机
Actually you are just AIs parrot

40
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:07,433
你回想一下
Think back for a moment

41
00:01:07,766 --> 00:01:10,366
上一次你用AI做重要决定
The last time you used AI to make an important decision

42
00:01:10,566 --> 00:01:12,733
是真的自己想清楚了的
Did you really think it through yourself

43
00:01:12,766 --> 00:01:17,400
还是看了AI的答案之后觉得嗯好像有道理就拍了板
Or did you just see AIs answer think hmm seems reasonable and make the call

44
00:01:17,566 --> 00:01:19,900
心理学上有个概念叫自动化偏见
There is a concept in psychology called automation bias

45
00:01:20,066 --> 00:01:21,233
简单说就是
Simply put

46
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:25,633
人天然倾向于相信机器的判断
People naturally tend to trust machine judgments

47
00:01:25,866 --> 00:01:27,600
胜过相信自己的判断
More than their own

48
00:01:27,766 --> 00:01:28,800
研究表明
Research shows

49
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,800
当人类和AI给出不同建议时
When humans and AI give different suggestions

50
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,533
即使AI是错的
Even when AI is wrong

51
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:36,333
人们依然有85%的概率选择相信AI
People still have an 85 percent chance of choosing to trust AI

52
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,366
85%
85 percent

53
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:40,333
也就是说10个人里有8个半
That means out of 10 people 8 and a half

54
00:01:40,566 --> 00:01:42,433
在AI和自己的判断之间
Between AI and their own judgment

55
00:01:42,433 --> 00:01:43,233
会选AI
Will choose AI

56
00:01:43,433 --> 00:01:45,700
哪怕AI那个答案是错的
Even if that AI answer is wrong

57
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:46,200
好
OK

58
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,166
现在注意听
Now pay attention

59
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:48,533
接下来的内容
What comes next

60
00:01:48,633 --> 00:01:53,300
可能会让你重新审视你每天都在用的AI工具
Might make you rethink the AI tools you use every day

61
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,200
因为真正危险的
Because what is truly dangerous

62
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,100
不是AI给出的答案本身
Is not the answer AI gives itself

63
00:01:58,266 --> 00:02:00,600
而是你在接收这个答案的过程中
But rather during the process of receiving that answer

64
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:03,100
你的大脑偷偷做了三件事
Your brain secretly does three things

65
00:02:03,266 --> 00:02:04,100
第一件
First

66
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,500
锚定
Anchoring

67
00:02:05,766 --> 00:02:07,600
AI给你的第一个数字
The first number AI gives you

68
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:09,000
成了你的天花板
Becomes your ceiling

69
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:10,166
第二件
Second

70
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,600
确认
Confirmation

71
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:13,733
你不是在用AI搜索答案
You are not using AI to search for answers

72
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:16,133
你是在用AI找同意你的答案
You are using AI to find answers that agree with you

73
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,166
第三件
Third

74
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,600
框架
Framing

75
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:19,700
同一个事实
The same fact

76
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,333
AI换种说法
AI phrases it differently

77
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,433
你就做了完全不同的选择
And you make a completely different choice

78
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:24,933
我们一个一个讲
Let us go through them one by one

79
00:02:25,166 --> 00:02:26,300
先讲第一个
Let us start with the first one

80
00:02:26,366 --> 00:02:28,600
这个偏差一旦你理解了
Once you understand this bias

81
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,533
你会发现你每天都在中招
You will realize you fall for it every day

82
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,000
你打开ChatGPT
You open ChatGPT

83
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,733
问它
Ask it

84
00:02:32,733 --> 00:02:35,100
你觉得我这个年终奖该不该跳槽
Should I change jobs with this year end bonus

85
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,766
AI分析了一大堆
AI analyzes a whole bunch

86
00:02:36,766 --> 00:02:37,900
最后说了一句
And finally says

87
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,900
建议薪资涨幅低于30%不建议跳槽
Suggests that if the salary increase is below 30 percent it is not recommended to change jobs

88
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:44,300
然后你去跟HR谈薪资
Then you go negotiate salary with HR

89
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,600
HR给了你20%的涨幅
HR offers you a 20 percent increase

90
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,933
你心里怎么想
What do you think in your heart

91
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:48,966
才20%
Only 20 percent

92
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,200
不够
Not enough

93
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:51,366
但问题是
But here is the thing

94
00:02:51,933 --> 00:02:55,033
如果AI没跟你说30%这个数字
If AI had not told you the number 30 percent

95
00:02:55,266 --> 00:02:56,966
你觉得20%的涨幅
Do you think a 20 percent increase

96
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,633
你会觉得不够吗
Would you feel it is not enough

97
00:02:58,833 --> 00:02:59,833
大概率不会
Probably not

98
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,900
你甚至会觉得不错了
You might even think it is pretty good

99
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:04,200
AI给你的第一个数字
The first number AI gives you

100
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,300
没有增加你的信息
Does not add to your information

101
00:03:06,766 --> 00:03:09,166
它只是锁死了你的期望
It just locks in your expectations

102
00:03:09,266 --> 00:03:11,366
这在心理学上叫锚定效应
In psychology this is called the anchoring effect

103
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:12,800
1974年
In 1974

104
00:03:13,033 --> 00:03:16,100
特沃斯基和卡尼曼做过一个经典实验
Tversky and Kahneman conducted a classic experiment

105
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:18,600
他们在一个转盘上随机转出一个数字
They spun a random number on a wheel

106
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,600
0到100之间
Between 0 and 100

107
00:03:20,733 --> 00:03:22,166
然后问被试者
Then asked the participants

108
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,800
联合国里非洲国家的比例
The percentage of African countries in the United Nations

109
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:27,333
是高于还是低于这个数字
Is higher or lower than this number

110
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:28,500
结果发现
The results showed

111
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,100
转到65的人
Those who landed on 65

112
00:03:30,266 --> 00:03:31,433
平均猜45%
On average guessed 45 percent

113
00:03:32,066 --> 00:03:33,166
转到10的人
Those who landed on 10

114
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:34,400
平均猜25%
On average guessed 25 percent

115
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,900
一个完全随机的数字
A completely random number

116
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:39,500
就把人的判断拉偏了20个百分点
Skewed peoples judgments by 20 percentage points

117
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:39,833
好
OK

118
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:41,033
记住这个实验
Remember this experiment

119
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,700
现在我们回到AI
Now let us go back to AI

120
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,533
AI给你的第一个答案
The first answer AI gives you

121
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:47,000
就是那个转盘上的随机数字
Is like that random number on the wheel

122
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,833
它看起来很专业
It looks very professional

123
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:49,733
很权威
Very authoritative

124
00:03:49,733 --> 00:03:50,833
有理有据
Well reasoned

125
00:03:51,266 --> 00:03:53,100
但它给你的作用
But its effect on you

126
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,733
和那个随机数字一模一样
Is exactly the same as that random number

127
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:58,633
你现在去翻翻你跟ChatGPT的聊天记录
Go check your ChatGPT chat history now

128
00:03:58,766 --> 00:04:00,300
看看你问的每一个问题
Look at every question you asked

129
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,133
AI给你的第一个回答
The first answer AI gives you

130
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,633
你是不是基本都在围绕它思考
Are you mostly just thinking around it

131
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,766
有没有真正跳出来想过
Have you ever truly stepped back and thought

132
00:04:06,866 --> 00:04:08,633
如果AI不说这个数字
If AI did not mention this number

133
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:10,200
我自己会怎么判断
How would I judge it myself

134
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:13,000
锚定效应在商业上用得太多了
The anchoring effect is used so much in business

135
00:04:13,133 --> 00:04:14,366
你去买一件衣服
You go buy a piece of clothing

136
00:04:14,366 --> 00:04:15,533
标价299
Price tag 299

137
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:16,833
你心里想
You think to yourself

138
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,200
太贵了
Too expensive

139
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,233
然后旁边贴了个原价
Then you see the original price next to it

140
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:21,233
599
599

141
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,100
划掉
Crossed out

142
00:04:22,133 --> 00:04:23,300
现价299
Now 299

143
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,633
你立刻觉得
You immediately feel

144
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:25,566
哇
Wow

145
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:26,300
赚了
What a deal

146
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:28,233
599这个数字就是锚
The number 599 is the anchor

147
00:04:28,466 --> 00:04:30,400
它让你觉得299很便宜
It makes you think 299 is cheap

148
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,966
但这件衣服的成本可能就50块
But this piece of clothing might only cost 50 to make

149
00:04:33,066 --> 00:04:34,233
你不是省了300
You did not save 300

150
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:36,333
你是被300这个锚锁住了
You are locked by the anchor of 300

151
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:38,400
AI在做同样的事
AI is doing the exact same thing

152
00:04:38,566 --> 00:04:40,633
它给你的价格建议
The price suggestions it gives you

153
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:41,900
薪资预期
Salary expectations

154
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:43,333
投资回报率
Return on investment

155
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,900
这些数字一旦出现在你面前
Once these numbers appear in front of you

156
00:04:46,066 --> 00:04:47,233
就成了你的锚
They become your anchors

157
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,233
你之后的所有思考
All your thinking afterwards

158
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:51,233
都是在围绕这个锚打转
Just revolves around this anchor

159
00:04:51,466 --> 00:04:52,800
更危险的是
What is more dangerous is

160
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,800
AI有时候连自己都不知道自己在锚定你
Sometimes AI does not even know it is anchoring you

161
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,000
2023年
In 2023

162
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,633
有一项研究让两组人估算一个项目的成本
A study had two groups estimate the cost of a project

163
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,400
第一组没有AI辅助
The first group had no AI assistance

164
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,733
第二组用了AI
The second group used AI

165
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,800
结果呢
And the result

166
00:05:05,966 --> 00:05:07,333
用AI的那组
The group that used AI

167
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:08,800
给出的估算数字
The estimates they gave

168
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:11,800
和AI第一次给出的数字高度重合
Highly overlapped with the number AI first gave

169
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:13,366
偏差不到5%
Deviation less than 5 percent

170
00:05:13,866 --> 00:05:14,866
没用的那组
The group that did not use AI

171
00:05:14,866 --> 00:05:16,700
人跟人之间的差异很大
Had huge differences between people

172
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,433
有人估高有人估低
Some estimated high some estimated low

173
00:05:18,466 --> 00:05:21,333
但平均下来反而更接近真实成本
But on average it was actually closer to the real cost

174
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:23,066
用了AI的那组
The group that used AI

175
00:05:23,066 --> 00:05:26,700
所有人都挤在了AI给的那个数字附近
Everyone crowded around the number AI gave

176
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,500
AI没有帮你做出更好的判断
AI did not help you make better judgments

177
00:05:29,966 --> 00:05:32,500
它只是让所有人都做出了同样的判断
It just made everyone make the same judgment

178
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:33,333
你想想
Think about it

179
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,000
你现在做任何重要决定之前
Before you make any important decision now

180
00:05:36,366 --> 00:05:38,633
是不是第一反应都是先问AI
Is your first reaction always to ask AI first

181
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:39,700
如果是
If so

182
00:05:40,366 --> 00:05:41,733
你已经被锚了
You have already been anchored

183
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:42,833
但等一下
But wait

184
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,633
锚定只是第一个陷阱
Anchoring is only the first trap

185
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,333
还有一个更隐蔽的
There is an even more hidden one

186
00:05:46,466 --> 00:05:48,933
第二个偏差叫确认偏误
The second bias is called confirmation bias

187
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,166
听起来很学术
Sounds very academic

188
00:05:50,166 --> 00:05:51,400
但你一定中过招
But you have definitely fallen for it

189
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,066
你觉得自己是对的
You think you are right

190
00:05:53,066 --> 00:05:55,900
所以你去找证据证明自己是对的
So you look for evidence to prove you are right

191
00:05:55,966 --> 00:05:58,766
你会选择性地看到支持你的信息
You selectively see information that supports you

192
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,133
自动忽略反对你的信息
And automatically ignore information that contradicts you

193
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:02,133
现在有了AI
Now with AI

194
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:04,033
这个过程变得更可怕了
This process has become even more terrifying

195
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,666
你打开ChatGPT
You open ChatGPT

196
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:06,433
问它
Ask it

197
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,633
2026年买房是不是一个好时机
Is 2026 a good time to buy a house

198
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,600
如果你自己心里觉得不该买
If deep down you feel you should not buy

199
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,133
你大概率不会这么问
You probably would not ask it that way

200
00:06:12,266 --> 00:06:13,066
你会问
You would ask

201
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:15,333
2026年房价会不会跌
Will housing prices drop in 2026

202
00:06:15,466 --> 00:06:16,333
发现了吗
Notice the pattern

203
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:19,733
你的提问方式本身就已经暴露了你的立场
The way you ask the question already reveals your stance

204
00:06:19,866 --> 00:06:22,166
AI不是在帮你做判断
AI is not helping you make a judgment

205
00:06:22,166 --> 00:06:23,800
它是在帮你找理由
It is helping you find reasons

206
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:26,100
支持你已经做好的判断
To support the judgment you already made

207
00:06:26,233 --> 00:06:27,566
心理学研究发现
Psychology research has found

208
00:06:27,566 --> 00:06:29,766
当人们用搜索引擎
When people use search engines

209
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:31,966
不管是Google还是AI
Whether Google or AI

210
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:33,833
来验证自己的观点时
To verify their own views

