00:12:58,866 --> 00:13:02,366
给我5个不应该在这个时候买房的理由
Give me 5 reasons not to buy a house right now

402
00:13:02,466 --> 00:13:04,166
然后你看这两个答案
Then look at both answers

403
00:13:04,266 --> 00:13:05,433
你自己做判断
And make your own judgment

404
00:13:05,566 --> 00:13:08,166
这个方法直接攻击了确认偏误
This method directly attacks confirmation bias

405
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,833
你不再是只看你想看的
You are no longer only seeing what you want to see

406
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,533
你主动逼自己看另一面
You actively force yourself to see the other side

407
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:16,600
真正的高手不是只看自己想看的
Real experts do not just look at what they want to see

408
00:13:16,733 --> 00:13:18,400
是两面的信息都看完了
They look at information from both sides

409
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,633
还能做出判断
And still make a judgment

410
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,000
这种能力
This kind of ability

411
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,500
叫灰度思维
Is called gray thinking

412
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:24,366
每次问AI一个问题
Every time you ask AI a question

413
00:13:24,466 --> 00:13:26,600
就再追问一句反面的
Follow up with the opposite

414
00:13:26,766 --> 00:13:27,933
养成习惯
Make it a habit

415
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,933
你会发现自己做的决定
You will find the decisions you make

416
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:31,433
质量完全不一样了
Are of completely different quality

417
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,800
第三个方法
The third method

418
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,966
叫脱框架思考
Is called deframing thinking

419
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,300
记住一件事
Remember one thing

420
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:38,533
AI回答你的方式
The way AI answers you

421
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,900
只是无数种可能的表达方式之一
Is just one of countless possible ways to express it

422
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:44,033
当你看到AI的答案时
When you see AIs answer

423
00:13:44,266 --> 00:13:47,433
试着在心里把它翻过来重新说一遍
Try to mentally flip it and rephrase it

424
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,100
AI说这个产品过去一年涨了30%
AI says this product went up 30 percent in the past year

425
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:53,800
你心里翻成这个产品还有70%没涨
You mentally flip it to this product still has 70 percent that did not go up

426
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,200
AI说这个岗位的月薪比行业平均高5000
AI says this positions monthly salary is 5000 higher than the industry average

427
00:13:57,200 --> 00:14:01,133
你心里翻成这个行业平均月薪只有这么多
You mentally flip it to the industry average monthly salary is only this much

428
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,900
这不是文字游戏
This is not a word game

429
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:05,333
每次你主动转换框架
Every time you actively switch frames

430
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,300
你就在训练自己的系统二
You are training your own system two

431
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,533
那个慢的
The slow one

432
00:14:08,566 --> 00:14:09,433
理性的
The rational one

433
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:11,433
需要费力的思考系统
The effort requiring thinking system

434
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,433
金融行业有个术语叫压力测试
The finance industry has a term called stress testing

435
00:14:14,566 --> 00:14:19,566
就是故意用最极端的框架来审视一个投资决策
Which means deliberately using the most extreme frame to examine an investment decision

436
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:22,000
你用AI的时候也可以这么做
You can do the same when using AI

437
00:14:22,466 --> 00:14:23,300
问AI
Ask AI

438
00:14:23,566 --> 00:14:26,433
如果用最悲观的眼光看这个问题
If you look at this problem from the most pessimistic perspective

439
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:27,500
会怎样
What would happen

440
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:28,966
脱框架思考
Deframing thinking

441
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:32,200
不要只看AI给你的那面镜子
Do not just look at the mirror AI gives you

442
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,233
走过去
Walk over

443
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,900
看看镜子的背面
Look at the back of the mirror

444
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:35,966
三个方法
Three methods

445
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,266
先想后问
Think first ask later

446
00:14:37,266 --> 00:14:38,300
对抗锚定
Against anchoring

447
00:14:38,466 --> 00:14:39,566
红队提问
Red team questioning

448
00:14:39,566 --> 00:14:40,966
对抗确认偏误
Against confirmation bias

449
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,533
脱框架思考
Deframing thinking

450
00:14:42,566 --> 00:14:44,166
对抗框架效应
Against framing effect

451
00:14:44,266 --> 00:14:47,200
AI是这个时代最强大的工具之一
AI is one of the most powerful tools of this era

452
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,000
但工具的价值
But the value of a tool

453
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:50,800
取决于使用工具的人
Depends on the person using it

454
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,100
你现在想想
Think about it now

455
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:55,000
上一次你用AI做了什么重要决定
What important decision did you last make using AI

456
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,200
那个决定
That decision

457
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,566
是你做的
Did you make it

458
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,033
还是AI帮你做的
Or did AI make it for you

459
00:14:59,166 --> 00:15:00,233
如果你不确定
If you are not sure

460
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:02,000
那大概率是后者
Then it is most likely the latter

461
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:03,733
AI不会替你做决定
AI will not make decisions for you

462
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,700
它只是让你以为
It just makes you think

463
00:15:05,766 --> 00:15:07,566
那个决定是你自己做的
That you made that decision yourself

464
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:10,566
在这个AI越来越强的时代
In this era where AI gets stronger and stronger

465
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,500
最值钱的能力不是会用AI
The most valuable skill is not knowing how to use AI

466
00:15:13,966 --> 00:15:16,400
是知道什么时候不该信AI
It is knowing when not to trust AI

467
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:19,133
所以下次打开ChatGPT之前
So next time before you open ChatGPT

468
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,300
给自己30秒
Give yourself 30 seconds

469
00:15:20,466 --> 00:15:21,433
先想后问
Think first ask later

470
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,733
你不需要比AI更聪明
You do not need to be smarter than AI

471
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:25,300
你只需要保证
You just need to make sure

472
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,366
那个最终拍板的人
The person who makes the final call

473
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:28,233
是你自己
Is you

474
00:15:28,433 --> 00:15:29,966
AI给你答案
AI gives you an answer

475
00:15:30,066 --> 00:15:32,033
不代表那个答案是对的
Does not mean that answer is right

476
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:34,333
更不代表那个答案是你的
Even less does it mean that answer is yours

477
00:15:34,466 --> 00:15:35,733
真正的聪明
True intelligence

478
00:15:35,733 --> 00:15:37,433
不是找到最好的答案
Is not finding the best answer

479
00:15:37,566 --> 00:15:39,300
而是确保那个答案
But making sure that answer

480
00:15:39,366 --> 00:15:41,233
真的经过了你的大脑
Truly passed through your brain

481
00:15:41,366 --> 00:15:43,933
如果你觉得今天的内容对你有启发
If you found todays content inspiring

482
